{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, synchronous checkpointing solutions, e.g.",
    "default checkpointing implemented in DeepSpeed [34], that block the training until the model state is captured to stable storage incur high runtime overheads.",
    "Alternatively, one may use a multi-level asynchronous checkpointing solution that copies the model state to a fast memory tier and then flushes it from there to slower tiers in the background without blocking the training.",
    "In general, this is a widely used solution in the HPC community that successfully reduces the runtime overheads compared with synchronous checkpointing.",
    "However, it is not straightforward to implement this approach in the context of LLM training for two reasons."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "default checkpointing implemented in DeepSpeed [34], that block the training until the model state is captured to stable storage incur high runtime overheads."
  ]
}